-- Ghana Oil Rises to Record High After 2012 Profit Jumped 32%
-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 2013-02-01T15:09:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-01/ghana-oil-rises-to-record-high-after-2012-profit-jumped-32-.html
Ghana Oil Co. (GOIL) , the second-biggest
operator of fuel stations in the West African nation, rose to
the highest on record after saying profit increased 32 percent
in 2012.  The stock climbed for a third day, adding 1.5 percent to
close at 69 pesewas by 3 p.m. in the capital, Accra. Thatâ€™s the
highest since the company listed on the Ghana Stock Exchange in
November 2007, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Net income increased to 10.4 million cedis ($5.5 million),
the company said in a statement published in the Business and
Financial Times newspaper today. Revenue advanced to 791.3
million cedis from 610.5 million cedis a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
